I've known my best friend for 14 years now. We got along so well, ever since we were toddlers. She was never explicitly mean to me; we had our moments but we always made up again. She was one of my only friends for a very long time.
In 8th grade, she befriended another kid in our grade. This kid had it rough: they were held back, struggling with mental issues of their own, and their dad passed away not long after. So I gave them the benefit of the doubt and welcomed them, hoping we'd form a friend group or something.
However, quarantine happened, and I stopped hanging out with this friend weekly because we weren't allowed to. In that time, we both became more active online and talked to each other on Discord, in addition to other platforms. She also started talking more to this other friend. They made nicknames for each other, and we both proclaimed ourselves as her "wife". 
Lockdown relaxed a bit near the end of our freshman year, but our hangouts didn't return to normal. We still talked, but we were never put in classes together, never in the same lunch period, and she was much more active on platforms I wasn't used to, such as Snapchat. She often posted pics and videos on Instagram and Tiktok featuring this other friend. I was happy that they were having a good time, even if I wasn't invited. By that time, I had made quite a few online friends anyway. I just figured we were letting each other hang out with our other friends. Since we're neighbors, my mom would drive us both home from school, giving us a chance to talk. She always had so much more to say than me, since I was never the most social person and didn't often get into drama.
The only time we saw each other over the summer was at ours and others' birthday parties. Most of the time, we just stayed inside and spent our time alone, but occasionally I would see her post about doing things with her other friend. Every time I tried inviting her somewhere, it was at an inconvenient time or she was just too tired. 
As junior year and the present approached, I started getting increasingly more worried that I was losing her; one of my best and closest friends for over a decade. We started taking the bus instead of being driven to school, and she sat several seats behind me, in a two-seater that two people couldn't fit in. She started talking to her other friends much more than me, and I was stricken with the fear that I was now cramping her style, and that she was trying to avoid me so she wouldn't be perceived as weird. She barely talks to me now, and I wholeheartedly feel that the role I took as a kid has been replaced. I still want to stay friends with her and hang out with her more, but I'm starting to give up.
If you happen to read this, I don't have anything against you. I'm still struggling to cope with losing such a close friend, and I hope high school isn't what makes us part.

i stopped liking her last year after she was caught doing some rather problematic things (and then apologized for them and kept doing it, like... dude) and i started really paying attention to her lyrics, how they're actually pretty misandrist and kind of mean-spirited. that in mind, there are songs from her that i totally get why people like them. some of which are actually pretty decent.

i have never understood the appeal of this song (the fact it has a very overrated video doesn't help matters). i do kind of like the musical ideas here: it's got that late 2000s emo ballad vibe reminiscent of early panic! at the disco or paramore before hayley went the gwen stefani route. i could probably talk myself into liking it if it were about anything else and if the lyrics were better: i apologize to anyone ahead of time who relates to them but these lyrics actually kind of suck.

i've been through plenty of shit myself - suffered from major depression, anxiety, came from a dysfunctional family with alcoholic parents and spent my childhood in a trailer, suffered from body image issues far worse than her (if you can believe that), used to cut, had anorexia in middle school and a good portion of high school, homeless at one point, almost had the place i was staying at burn down in a wildfire, almost went to the psych ward, and i almost died, twice - but these lyrics don't do anything for me (corin tucker yelling "why can't i get along with you?" about 5 or 6 times in sleater-kinney's song "far away", a song about 9/11, is more heartbreaking to me than this). not to mention, the song "male fantasy", which comes right after this, renders the message of this song completely pointless. sometimes you can't end things on a good note, billie. sometimes you have to leave it because there's nothing you can do. i don't think that song is a "good note" anyways, but that's beside my point, though.

also, the way she keeps promoting this song reminds me of madonna promoting her song "hollywood" about 20 years ago and dropping it in at every whim. except the fact it's this song and not something else... it makes it and also her that much more unlikable and for me it confirms her whole "not like other girls" mindset. "i'm not like other singers. i have a single that's actually a rock song"... yeah, that'd be fine... if pop punk and pop rock haven't been things for decades. plus, there's been this whole thing going on the past few years, before she showed up with this, mind, where pop singers started doing rock songs and *it just doesn't work with her*. you can't be a rock singer who doesn't like to sing powerfully - or one who shoves her "screams" way off in the background. halsey and poppy do better screams than this mainly because they're right there in your ear but also because they actually seem more genuine. yeah. miss "i'm all about being real and authentic" comes off as kind of phony with those distant yells in the latter part.

but much like madonna, what is billie without her hits? number 1 or not, this is without question her worst song and i don't understand why people are so moist over it when it's so lame... especially in a time like this. after the last 3 years we've had, we need a song like this like we need holes in our heads. not to mention... charting shouldn't tell you squat about quality, anyways. the best songs in the world are virtually unknown or unfairly put down because overrated nonsense like this is charting.

It hurt not relating to him anymore. 
The worst part was me being in love with him. 
He knew it, he knew it and used against me, claiming I was a jealous freak. 
He and his friend group planned to confront  me about my jealousy and other things during my after-graduation party, I ended up not going for my own safety, since they were many and I was only one. 
Ruined my school years, ruined every single good moment we spent together, my graduation day was one of the saddest, I never felt so out of place. 
That friend group kinda had the whole class on a tight leash, so it felt like everyone was against me. 
I‚Äôd been in love before with friends that were in relationships, he should know I‚Äôd never flirt or try anything with him because of it.

The last day I saw him in person, I thought of talking to him, to apologizing for not being good enough, but then I saw him smiling with his group of friends while taking a selfie and I though twice: maybe he‚Äôs better off without me for real. So I left and never looked back.
I still miss and I still feel for him. What exactly? A mix of nostalgia, sadness, anger and an annoying bit of love that refuses to die down. 
Sorry for ranting, I just needed to get this out of my chest.
At least I still have my friend group, it may not last forever, but for now I‚Äôm incredibly happy with them.
They‚Äôre the best I could ever have and for the first time in 18 years I feel at home with a group of people, feel like I belong.

Hi. I have something important to share. Will you listen? 

"As it is written: 'There is no one righteous, not even one.' "- Romans 3:10   "for all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God"- Romans 3:23 

So what does this mean? Well, let's look into it :) 

"The Lord has disciplined me severely, But He has not given me over to death." - Psalm 118: 18  The psalmist (the person speaking) is talking about how the Lord has disciplined him. To discipline is to reprimand or punish for a wrongdoing. This shows that the psalmist has sinned before. Therefore, he is not righteous right? It would seem like it, but then the psalmist continues on...

 "Open to me the gates of righteousness; I shall enter through them, I shall give thanks to the Lord. This is the gate of the Lord; The righteous will enter through it." Psalm 118:19-20 

So now the psalmist is entering the gates of the righteous. Something that only the righteous can do.  How is this possible? How can someone who has sinned be righteous before God? I mean God hates sin how can someone who has sinned be in right standing with him? Well let's find out. 

"I shall give thanks to You, for You have answered me, And You have become my salvation." - Psalm 118:21 

It is "You" who has become his salvation; "You" has saved him. But how? And just who is this "You" anyway? 

The psalmist answers this question by saying "The stone which the builders rejected Has become the chief corner stone." Psalm 118: 22 

What stone? Jesus. Jesus Christ is "The stone which the builders rejected...." -Psalm 118: 22 for "He was despised and rejected by mankind, a man of suffering, and familiar with pain. Like one from whom people hide their faces he was despised, and we held him in low esteem." Isaiah 53:3 

But he has become the most important piece.  Jesus said "I and the Father are one.‚Äù - John 10:30  (The father being God) "Jesus said to him, ‚ÄúI am the way, and the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me." -John 14:6

For "This Jesus is ‚Äòthe stone you builders rejected, which has become the cornerstone.‚Äô Salvation exists in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given to men by which we must be saved.‚Äù -Acts 4:11-12

But wait, we still don't know how Jesus can possibly save us. Let's look into that. As we continue further along in the passage it says, "The Lord is God, and He has given us light; Bind the festival sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar." -Psalm 118:27

The horns of the alter was a symbol of the death of the sacrifice. People would take hold of the horns of the alter to attain mercy. Jesus died on the cross so that we could obtain mercy. He was the sacrifice. Just like the psalmist, we have all sinned, and are deserving of hell. We all fall short, but.... right after Romans 3:23 (the verse that says that we fall short) comes Romans 3:24 " being justified as a gift by His grace through the redemption which is in Christ Jesus,"


Through Jesus we can be justified and made righteous. Not by doing anything to earn it. Not by working hard enough, or praying enough, or reading/ studying enough, or even because of the good things we do for others or God. Only  through the sacrifice that Jesus made on the cross can we appeal to God for mercy and be in right standing with Him. Not that we deserved anything, but as an unearned gift.

 Jesus loves every single one of you. (And so does God that's why he sent his son Jesus) That is why he gave up his life for you. He died so that you could be free. The punishment for sin is death. (the second death is hell.) But Jesus died to pay for our sins. "God presented Him as the atoning sacrifice through faith in His blood...." -Romans 3:25  He died for us, but then he rose again. Doing what we couldn't have done, defeating sin and the grave. 

Do you believe that you are a sinner in need of a savior? Do you believe in the Good news that Jesus came to die for the sins of the world on the cross (and then rose again/resurrected)? Well then...

"Then he brought them out and asked, ‚ÄúSirs, what must I do to be saved?‚Äù They replied, ‚ÄúBelieve in the Lord Jesus and you will be saved, you and your household.‚Äù‚Äù -Acts 16:30-31

"that if you confess with your mouth Jesus as Lord, and believe in your heart that God raised Him from the dead, you will be saved"  -Romans 10:9


Being saved is just the beginning. Now that you are in right standing with God. You can have a relationship with him. He wants to talk to you. Do you wanna know him? He hears all that you say. ( Tell him everything; your plans, worries, fears, memories, problems, everything.) Read your Bible because that is one of the primary ways that God will speak back. He'll show you who he is. He'll let you find him if you seek him. :) He'll teach you how to live a life in freedom from sin. He'll give you the power to repent. Trust in Him He loves you. ‚ù§‚ù§
